<p style="color:white;">Mandalorian is an American space Western television series created by<br>
Jon Favreau for the streaming service Disney+. It is the first live-action <br>
series in the Star Wars franchise, beginning five years after the events<br>
of Return of the Jedi (1983). It stars Pedro Pascal as the title character,<br>
a lone bounty hunter who goes on the run after being hired to retrieve "The Child".</p>

<p style="color:white;">Star Wars creator George Lucas had begun developing a live-action <br>
Star Wars television series by 2009, but this project was deemed too<br>
 expensive to produce. He sold Lucasfilm to Disney in October 2012. <br>
 Subsequently, work on a new Star Wars series began for Disney+.<br>
 Favreau signed on in March 2018, serving as writer and showrunner.<br>
 He executive produces alongside Dave Filoni, Kathleen Kennedy,<br>
 and Colin Wilson. The series' title was announced in October 2018,<br>
 with filming starting at Manhattan Beach Studios in California.<br>
 Visual effects company Industrial Light & Magic developed<br>
 the StageCraft technology for the series, using virtual <br>
 sets and a 360-degree video wall to create the series' environments.<br>
 This has since been adopted by other film and television productions.</p>

<p style="color:white;">The Mandalorian premiered with the launch of Disney+ on November 12, 2019.<br>
 The eight-episode first season was met with positive reviews, <br>
 was nominated for Outstanding Drama Series at the 72nd Primetime <br>
 Emmy Awards, and won seven Primetime Creative Arts Emmy Awards.<br>
 A second season premiered on October 30, 2020, to positive reviews,<br>
 and a third season, which is currently filming, is expected to be released in 2022.<br>
 Several spin-off series will expand on the series' timeframe, <br>
 including The Book of Boba Fett and Ahsoka.</p>
